
// This code snippet uses the [set-value] slot to change the value of the node referenced by [.anchor]. It utilizes the [strings.replace] slot to replace all occurrences of the carriage return character ("\r") in the [.anchor] node with a space (" "). The [set-value] slot updates the node's value with the result of the [strings.replace] operation.
set-value:x:@.anchor
   strings.replace:x:@.anchor
      .:"\r"
      .:" "
